                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Dec. 14th&#47;88<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Dr&#33;<lb/></p>
            <p>I have been informed<lb/> that there is to be an examination of<lb/> the Seminary at the end of this<lb/> month.  Could you perhaps let me<lb/> know the date of the same and<lb/> also whether it is to be public or<lb/> private&#44; also whether we are to have<lb/> a meeting of the Advisory Board<lb/> previously or not.  Mr Friedlander<lb/> has applied for leave of absence<lb/> until the Summer Semester as<lb/> he is at present attending the<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>Evening High School and says<lb/> that he cannot attend both insti&#45;<lb/>&#45;tutions simultaneously.<lb/></p>
            <p>The Joseph Corn whom I was<lb/> looking up for you does not<lb/> live at the address given and<lb/> I was unable to find anyone<lb/> acquainted with his present<lb/> whereabouts.  I remain&#44; with<lb/> best regards<lb/> Yours truly<lb/> Bernard Drachman<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
